The bug in your code is that you're reinitializing `total` to `0` every loo
loop, so it always keeps adding the current item amount to `0`. To fix this
this issue, just remove or comment out the line where you initialize `total
`total` back to 0 inside the loop. Here's how it should look:

```tundra
val items = [
  { amount: 2 },
  { amount: 5 },
  { amount: 7 }
];

var total = 0;
for (item in items) {
  total = total + item.amount;
}

print(total);
```
